@node install "Installing"
How to Install:

	o  First EDIT ALL the SCRIPTS! There is some variables which
	   need modifying! (edit only *.DRX files)

	   there is for example:

		'ModListName' - your ModuleList (Program list)
		'PlayerPath'  - pathname for DasModPlayer

	o  Copy ALL *.DRX files into REXX: directory.

	o  'PLAY' into S: or somewhere in command path!
	   'FadePlay' into S: too.

	Every  DOS-  and  AREXX-script  has  SCRIPT-flag  set so you can
	either use them with or without RX/EXECUTE.

@endnode

@node play "Play"
"Play"

	Just  a  simple  DOS  Script  utilizing "PlaySingle.DRX" script.
	Eases the use if you are just playing single modules from CLI.

	Type:		PLAY ModulePathName
			PLAY Module		(Plays from CurrentDir)

	Example:	PLAY dh0:data/modules/mod.ShwingingTheSwing
			PLAY MODULES:WalkOnJade.LHA
			PLAY ram:Yowl.mod.pp
			PLAY disharmony.lha

			PLAY MODULES:
				will play all modules from MODULES:-directory!

@endnode

@node fadeplay "FadePlay"
"FadePlay"

	Just  a simple DOS Script utilizing "PlaySingleFade.DRX" script.
	Eases the use if you are just playing single modules from CLI.

	Type:		FadePLAY ModulePathName
			FadePLAY Module		(Plays from CurrentDir)


	Example:	FadePLAY dh0:data/modules/mod.ShwingingTheSwing
			FadePLAY MODULES:WalkOnJade.LHA
			FadePLAY ram:Yowl.mod.pp
			FadePLAY disharmony.lha

@endnode

@node single "PlaySingle.DRX"
Play Single Module

	Play   Single   module   from   CLI.    This  Script  will  HIDE
	DASModPlayer!

	Call with following parameters:

	RX PlaySingle.DRX ModulePathName

	example:	RX PlaySingle.DRX DH0:Data/Modules/Mystery.LHA
	     or:	RX PlaySingle.DRX DH0:Data/Modules/Mystery.MOD
	     or:	RX PlaySingle.DRX DH0:Data/Modules/MOD.Mystery
	     or:	PlaySingle.DRX disharmony.lha	(current dir)

	(Or Without RX)

	If  path  for  the  module  is  not  specified then DAS will use
	DEFAULTMODULEPATH (specified in DasModulePlayers Config menu)

	If  ONLY  PATH  is specified as modulename then das will ADD ALL
	MODULES in this directory and start playing them.


	@{"SPECIAL BBS USAGE!!!!" link bbsusage}
@endnode

@node bbsusage "Special BBS Usage"
Using script in BBS
	
	If  you  have  a  BBS  with  MANY  modules  and your BBS program
	supports AREXX!  Then this is for you and might be for some use.

	I  have  DLG-software  and  have  configured the following in my
	FILEMENU:

	When  I press ':' DLG will start playing the current module with
	DasModPlayer.   This  has  proved to be REALLY NICE feature when
	ranking the modules.

	Following is an example for DLG Pro BBSes:

[ 1] Letter:                   :
[ 2] Executable: (path/name)   rx rexx:PlaySingle.DRX %File_Filepath%File_Filename
[ 4] Description:              Play Module
[ 5] Type:                     Executable
[ 6] Help File:                FILE_MAIN/:
[ 7] Lower level:              200
[ 8] Upper level:              255
[ 9] Hidden:                   YES
[10] Load type:                OVERLAY
[11] Ask user if sure:         NO
[12] Pend messages:            NO
[13] Cli mode:                 YES
[14] Pause on completion:      NO
[15] Log value:                None
[16] Activity string:
[17] Priority:                 DEFAULT
[18] Edit help file
@endnode

@node singlefade "Play Single with Fade"
Play Single with Fade

	This is same as PlaySingle.DRX but if DASModPlayer is running it
	will  fade the current module and THEN load new module and start
	playing

	Usage:

		RX PlaySingleFade.DRX {ModuleName}   (with or without path)
	or

		PlaySingleFade.DRX {ModuleName}      (with or without path)

@endnode

@node fadenext "Fade to next module in program list"
Fade to Next Module

	Simple  demoscript that will just fade the volume to 0 and start
	playing next module in the program list.

	Usage:

		RX Fade2Next.DRX
	or

		Fade2Next.DRX

	If DASModPlayer is not running, this script will run it and load
	your  Modulelist  (you  must  edit  the  script)  and then start
	playing the first module.

@endnode

@node random "Play Random Module"
Play Random module from Module List

	This simply selects a random module from the module list.

	Usage:

		RX PlayRandom.DRX
	or

		PlayRandom.DRX

	If DasModPlayer is not running, this will run it and load module
	list  (you  must edit the script) you have specified, then start
	playing first random module.

@endnode

@node faderandom "Fade to Random Module"
Fade to Random Next

	Simple  demoscript that will just fade the volume to 0 and start
	playing RANDOM module in the module list.

	execute with:

		RX Fade2Random.DRX
	or

		Fade2Random.DRX

	If DasModPlayer is not running, this will run it and load module
	list  (you  must edit the script) you have specified, then start
	playing first random module.

@endnode

@node quit "Quit"
Quit DasModPlayer

	This script simply stops playing modules and quits DasModPlayer

	Usage:

		RX QUIT.DRX
	or

		QUIT.DRX
@endnode

@node fadequit "Quit With FADE"

	This  script  fades  the  volume to 0 and then stops playing and
	quits DASModPlayer

	Usage:

		RX FadeQUIT.DRX
	or

		FadeQUIT.DRX
@endnode
